main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a bright, oval-shaped object in the sky over Morrisville, Pennsylvania, on 1/20/67.
interesting points: The object was observed for 35 minutes and was described as being very bright and blue-white in color,The observer indicated that the object appeared to be brighter than a star,The object's course was northwest to north,It was noted that the object seemed to hover and then disappeared from sight,The report suggests it could be a possible aircraft satellite.
witness description: civilian observer who noted the object's brightness and color
